facts.fact_text: Initial jobless claims in the US rose by 22,000 to 231,000 on the last week of January.

evidences.evidence_text: Initial jobless claims in the US rose by 22,000 from the previous week to 231,000 on the last week of January

facts.fact_text: The increase in initial jobless claims was above market expectations of 212,000.
Continuing claims rose by 25,000 to 1,844,000 in the previous week.

evidences.evidence_text: Consistently, continuing claims rose by 25,000 to 1,844,000 in the previous week

claims.claim_text: The results maintained the view that the US labor market remains in a low firing and low hiring trend.

evidences.evidence_text: Despite the evidence of softening, the results maintained the view that the US labor market remains in a low firing and low hiring trend.
